- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks and proposes a method to compress pre-trained language models such as BERT.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a knowledge distillation approach to compress a large model into a lightweight network, which is a common topic in machine learning research.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a method to improve the efficiency of large-scale model training, which is a key challenge in AI research.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the proposed method could potentially be applied to compress large models in computer vision tasks.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a method that involves incremental knowledge extraction from multiple intermediate layers of a model, which could be seen as a data structure or algorithmic approach.
